Male. Color. Similar to female. Dark pattern on face, vertex and clypeus less extensive, e.g., small yellow stripe between kidney-shaped spots and postocellar area usually present (
Fig. 49
). Antennae pale brown. Mesoscutum at most a little yellow anteriorly on lateral lobes. Abdomen brown, tergum 8 with pale blotch medially, hypopygium dirty yellowish brown.
